McDonald Et al donâ€™t specifically mention how they calculated the Trophic Enrichment/Discriminatory Factor, but I am assuming they used this equation, (Fry, 2006): Î”=Î´câˆ’Î´f where c refers to the isotopic signature/mixture of the consumer, and the f refers to the isotopic signature/mixture of the food source at equilibrium. Essentially, that occurs when the consumer has fed on the food long enough to where there signature values are no longer changing.
